<ContentPage
  title="Privacy Policy — What We Collect (Almost Nothing) | LazyTools"
  description="LazyTools processes everything in your browser: your files and inputs are never uploaded. We use no tracking, no analytics and no cookies — the only data we ever handle is standard host logs and opt-in anonymous tool ratings."
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  updated="July 12, 2026"
>
  <p>
    <strong>Plain-English summary:</strong> anything you type into a tool or any file you process stays on your
    device — we never receive it, so we can't store, sell or leak it. We run <strong>no analytics, no tracking
    and no cookies</strong>. The only data that ever touches a server is the standard technical logs any web host
    keeps, and — if you choose to rate a tool — an anonymous star rating that carries no personal information.
  </p>

  <h2>1. What we never collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>The values you type into tools, the files you process, and any results — all processing happens locally in your browser (<a href="/how-it-works/">how it works</a>), and none of it is ever transmitted.</li>
    <li>Accounts, names, or email addresses — there is no sign-up, and we hold no customer data.</li>
    <li>Analytics or tracking of any kind — no Google Analytics, no tracking pixels, no advertising or cross-site tracking, and <strong>no cookies</strong>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. What we do handle</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Standard server logs.</strong> Like every website, our hosting provider (Namecheap) automatically records basic web-server logs — IP address, requested URL and timestamp — for security and reliability. These are ordinary host logs, retained for a limited period; we do not use them to build profiles or track individuals.</li>
    <li><strong>Opt-in anonymous ratings.</strong> If — and only if — you click to rate a tool, we store just the tool's name and your star value (1–5), plus a timestamp. As the <a href="https://github.com/Synth88Labs/lazytools.io" rel="noopener">source code</a> shows, this records <strong>no IP address, no cookie, no user agent and no identifier</strong>. Whether you've rated a tool is remembered only in your own browser's local storage, never sent to us.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Legal bases and your rights (GDPR/CCPA)</h2>
  <p>
    Because we set <strong>no cookies and use no non-essential tracking</strong>, the EU ePrivacy consent
    requirement does not apply and there is no consent banner to manage. The only processing is the standard
    host logs described above, handled under legitimate interest (operating and securing a free service), and the
    ratings you voluntarily submit, handled with your consent. Since we hold no accounts and no personal data,
    most data-rights requests (access, deletion, portability) have nothing to act on — but you can always
    <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> with any privacy question or concern.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Third parties</h2>
  <p>
    We do not use advertisers, and we do not sell or share data. The only third party involved is our hosting
    provider, bound by its own privacy commitments. If this ever changes — for example, if analytics or ads were
    ever introduced — this policy and the site would say so clearly, in advance.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We'll update the "Last updated" date above whenever this policy materially changes, and summarize changes in
    plain language.
  </p>
</ContentPage>
